Class VOIDefaultColorModel

  ColorModel
      VOIColorModel

All Implemented Interfaces:
Transparency
public final class VOIDefaultColorModel
extends VOIColorModel

Color model used when no VOI LUT is used and when the standard Java color models are not suitable. This typically happens when the pixel values are signed.

VOIDefaultColorModel

public VOIDefaultColorModel(int ttype,
                            int bits,
                            ColorSpace cs)
Constructs a new VOIDefaultColorModel.

Parameters:
ttype - Transfer type, one of DataBuffer.TYPE_BYTE, DataBuffer.TYPE_SHORT, DataBuffer.TYPE_USHORT, and DataBuffer.TYPE_INT.
bits - number of significant bits, at least 8 and at most 16.
cs - Color space, must have 1 component.
